edas#SlideSet: MealMenu is a document that is parented to SlideSet. It is also the parent of MealEvent which has MealMenu.
edas#Review: RejectedPaper is the parent of both Paper and Review. It is also the child of RejectedPaper which is also the child of RejectedPaper.
edas#Programme: Document is a child of both Paper and PendingPaper. It is the parent of both Paper and SlideSet.
edas#Paper: The Paper isWrittenBy and isReviewedBy. The Author is the parent of the Presenter and the Reviewer. The ConferenceChair is the initiator of the Call. The Call is initiated by the SessionChair who is the parent of the presenter.
edas#MealMenu: The ConferenceChair is the parent of the non-AcademicEvent. The ConferenceEvent is the parent of the Paper and the RejectedPaper. MealEvent is the parent of the Paper and is the parent of MealMenu. MealEvent is the parent of the Paper and is the parent of the SlideSet.
edas#Document: The document is a child of SlideSet which is parented by the document. The person is the equivalent of the reviewer and the author.
edas#Topic: The ComputerNetworksTopic is the parent of Paper and the ComputerNetworksEnterpriseTopic. AcceptedPaper and WithdrawnPaper are both children of ComputerNetworksTopic.
edas#ConferenceEvent: BreakEvent is the parent of SocialEvent and ConferenceEvent. MealMenu is a food that is found in MealEvent. MealMenu is a food that is found in MealEvent.
edas#Call: ConferenceEvent is a non-academic event which is also known as BreakEvent. It is also known as a Conference. ConferenceChair is the parent of AcademicEvent which is also known as a Conference. ConferenceEvent is also known as a Conference. ConferenceEvent is also known as a Conference. BreakEvent is also known as a Conference. ConferenceEvent is also known as a Conference.
edas#ReviewRating: ReviewRating is equivalent to AcceptRating and WeekRejectRating.
edas#Organization: IndustryOrganization is a child of GovernmentOrganization and GovernmentOrganization.
edas#ReviewForm: The following table shows the percentage of people who are enrolled in the program.
edas#Conference: Conference is the parent of Thing.
edas#PersonalHistory: PersonalHistory is a child of PersonalReviewHistory and PersonalPublicationHistory.
edas#Sponsorship: AcademiaOrganization is the parent organization of AcademiaOrganization which is a NGO. AcademiaOrganization is the parent organization of AcademiaOrganization.
edas#ReviewQuestion: ReviewQuestion is a child of TextualReviewQuestion and NumericalReviewQuestion.
edas#Person: TPCMember is the parent of Paper which is relating to the AcademicEvent. Paper is also the child of the programme and is the parent of TPCMember who is the author of the document.
edas#Country: The following table shows the percentage of people who are enrolled in the program.
edas#ConferenceSession: The ConferenceSession hasRelatedDocument which is the child of the Paper which is the parent of the Conference. The Conference has registration due on the 1st of April. The Reviewer is the equivalent of a person who has written a personal review history.
edas#ContactInformation: The following table shows the percentage of people who are enrolled in the program.
edas#Place: ConferenceEvent is a non-academic event. It is attended by an attendee. It is held at DiningPlace which is the parent of the ConferenceEvent. The Document relating to the ConferenceSession is the Document relating to the ConferenceEvent.
edas#WeekRejectRating: ReviewRating is the parent of ReviewRating which is the equivalent of AccpetIfRoomRating and RejectRating.
edas#AccpetIfRoomRating: AccpetIfRoomRating is the parent of ReviewRating which is equivalent to AcceptRating and WeekRejectRating.
edas#RejectRating: ReviewRating is the parent of ReviewRating and is the child of AccpetIfRoomRating which is the equivalent of AcceptRating.
edas#MealEvent: BreakEvent and SocialEvent are both parents of MealEvent. MealEvent is a child of ConferenceDinner and Excursion. SocialEvent is a child of Reception and SocialEvent is a child of Excursion.
edas#NonAcademicEvent: MealMenu is a document that is part of the SlideSet. It is also part of the ConferenceEvent which is parented by MealEvent. MealMenu is also part of the ConferenceEvent and is located at the ConferenceEvent.
edas#BreakEvent: BreakEvent is the parent of SocialEvent and ConferenceDinner. It is also the parent of MealEvent and ConferenceDinner. BreakEvent is the equivalent of MealBreak.
edas#ParallelAndDistributedComputingTopi: The ParallelAndDistributedComputingTopic is the parent of the paper AntennasTopic which is reviewed by the SessionChair. The SessionChair is the parent of the person who is reviewing the Paper.
edas#WirelessCommunicationsTopic: The WirelessCommunicationsTopic is the parent of Paper which is reviewed by TPCMember. It is also the child of SlideSet and MealMenu. It is also the parent of Paper which is part of the Conference.
edas#OperatingTopicsystems: OperatingTopicsystems is the parent of CADTopic which is a paper which is written by the author. It is also the child of presenter and presenter and hasRelatedPaper which has a ReviewRating.
edas#ComputerNetworksTopic: ComputerNetworksSwitchingTopic is the parent of ComputerNetworksAapplicationsTopic which is also a child of ComputerNetworksSwitchingTopic.
edas#SatelliteAndSpaceCommunicationsTopi: SatelliteAndSpaceCommunicationsTopic is parented to ParallelAndDistributedComputingTopic and WirelessCommunicationsTopic.
edas#CADTopic: CADTopic is the parent of Paper which is the child of PowerlineTransmissionTopic. Paper is also the child of PendingPaper which is related to an AcademicEvent.
edas#MultimediaTopic: The MultimediaTopic is parented to the ComputerArchitectureTopic and the CommunicationTheoryTopic.
edas#CommunicationsTopic: The CommunicationsTopic is the parent of the ComputerArchitectureTopic which is the child of ParallelAndDistributedComputingTopic.
edas#PowerlineTransmissionTopic: The PowerlineTransmissionTopic is the parent of the Conference which is equivalent to the SingleLevelConference and the TwoLevelConference. The MobileComputingTopic is the child of the Conference.
edas#AntennasTopic: AntennasTopic is the parent of Conference which is equivalent to a SingleLevelConference. PerformanceTopic is the parent of Conference which has paperDueOn as a topic.
edas#PerformanceTopic: The MealMenu document is a child of the MealMenu and is a child of the RadioCommunicationsTopic. It is also a child of the Document which is the parent of the MealMenu.
edas#SignalProcessingTopic: AntennasTopic is the parent of SignalProcessingTopic which is the child of AntennasTopic. It is also the parent of Conference which is equivalent to TwoLevelConference.
edas#MicroelectronicsTopic: The MicroelectronicsTopic is the parent of the CommunicationTheoryTopic which is the topic of paper. The Document relating to the Conference is also the parent of the Document which is part of the programme.
edas#TestOnlyTopic: TestOnlyTopic is parented by both the CryptographyTopic and the PowerlineTransmissionTopic.
edas#RadioCommunicationsTopic: The RadioCommunicationsTopic is the parent of Paper which is a child of the PerformanceTopic. The Paper is also the parent of the PublishedPaper which is a child of the Programme.
edas#ComputerArchitectureTopic: The ComputerArchitectureTopic is the parent of the SatelliteAndSpaceCommunicationsTopic and the SecurityTopic.
edas#MedicineTopic: TestOnlyTopic and MedicineTopic are both parented by the same topic. MultimediaTopic and TestOnlyTopic are both children of TestOnlyTopic.
edas#SecurityTopic: PowerlineTransmissionTopic is a child of OperatingTopicsystems and SecurityTopic.
edas#MobileComputingTopic: The MobileComputingTopic is the parent of TestOnlyTopic and ParallelAndDistributedComputingTopic.
edas#CryptographyTopic: The CryptographyTopic is the parent of the Conference which is equivalent to the SingleLevelConference and the TwoLevelConference. The Conference is the parent of the CommunicationsTopic and the CryptographyTopic.
edas#CommunicationTheoryTopic: The CommunicationTheoryTopic is parented to the CryptographyTopic and OperatingTopicsystems.
edas#ConferenceChair: The ConferenceChair is the initiator of the Call for Manuscripts. The Paper is the parent of both the Paper and the SlideSet. The Document is the parent of both the CallForReviews and the CallForReviews.
edas#Author: WithdrawnPaper is the parent of Paper which is written by the author and hasRelatedPaper.
edas#DiningPlace: DiningPlace is the parent of ConferenceVenuePlace and ConferenceVenuePlace.
edas#Presenter: The presenter is the parent of the Author who is the parent of the person who is reviewing the paper. The paper is reviewed by the SessionChair who is the parent of the person who is reviewing the paper.
edas#AcademiaOrganization: AcademiaOrganization is parented by two organizations, IndustryOrganization and GovernmentOrganization.
edas#IndustryOrganization: The parent organization of IndustryOrganization is is isProviderOf. It is the parent organization of TravelGrant which is the parent organization of Sponsorship.
edas#NGO: AcademiaOrganization is the parent organization of AcademiaOrganization. IndustryOrganization is the parent organization of AcademiaOrganization.
edas#GovernmentOrganization: GovernmentOrganization is parented by TravelGrant which is a sponsor of TravelGrant. IndustryOrganization is parented by TravelGrant which is a sponsor of TravelGrant.
edas#ComputerNetworksEnterpriseTopic: The ComputerNetworksEnterpriseTopic is the parent of the ComputerNetworksEnterpriseTopic. It is also the parent of the CryptographyTopic which is the topic of the Conference. The Conference is the parent of Thing which is the conference's registration date.
edas#ComputerNetworksSwitchingTopic: The ComputerNetworksSwitchingTopic is the parent of the ComputerNetworksManagementTopic. It is also the parent of Paper which is part of the Conference. The Conference has a member and the Paper is part of the PublishedPaper.
edas#ComputerNetworksSensorTopic: The ComputerNetworksSensorTopic is the parent of the ComputerNetworksSecurityTopic. It is also the parent of the MultimediaTopic and CommunicationsTopic.
edas#ComputerNetworksSecurityTopic: The ComputerNetworksSecurityTopic is the parent of the ComputerNetworksManagementTopic. It is also the parent of the Medicine and WirelessCommunications topics.
edas#ComputerNetworksOpticalTopic: ComputerNetworksOpticalTopic is parented to ComputerNetworksManagementTopic. It is also parented to Medicine and Communications.
edas#ComputerNetworksMeasurementsTopic: The ComputerNetworksMeasurementsTopic is the parent of the ComputerNetworksSecurityTopic. It is also the parent of the OperatingTopicsystems and WirelessCommunicationsTopic.
edas#ComputerNetworksManagementTopic: The ComputerNetworksManagementTopic is the parent of the ComputerNetworksManagementTopic. The MultimediaTopic is also a parent of the ComputerNetworksManagementTopic.
edas#ComputerNetworksAapplicationsTopic: ComputerNetworksAapplicationsTopic is the parent of ComputerNetworksSecurityTopic and ComputerNetworksAapplicationsTopic.
edas#ActivePaper: WithdrawnPaper is the parent of Paper which is also a child of WithdrawnPaper. Paper is also a child of the Conference which is equivalent to a SingleLevelConference. Thing is also a parent of the Conference.
edas#PendingPaper: PendingPaper is the parent of Paper and AcceptedPaper. PublishedPaper is the parent of both Paper and AcceptedPaper.
edas#WithdrawnPaper: WithdrawnPaper is the parent of both Paper and MealMenu. MealMenu is a document that relates to the person who is a TPCM member. The attendee is a child of MealMenu.
edas#RejectedPaper: WithdrawnPaper is a child of Paper which is being reviewed by TPCMember. It is also the parent of Person who attends a Conference event and is the equivalent of Author.
edas#AcceptedPaper: AcceptedPaper is the parent of both Paper and Document. The document is also the child of SlideSet and Document.
edas#PublishedPaper: PendingPaper and RatedPapers are both children of Paper which is parented by both Paper and ActivePaper. Both Paper and RatedPaper have a ReviewRating.
edas#Attendee: The attendee is the parent of the ConferenceChair who is reviewing a document. The ConferenceChair is the parent of the person who is the equivalent of a Reviewer.
edas#CoffeeBreak: BreakEvent is the parent of CoffeeBreak which is the equivalent of MealBreak. It is also the parent of SocialEvent which is the child of Reception and NonAcademicEvent.
edas#FreeTimeBreak: BreakEvent is the parent of BreakEvent which is also the equivalent of MealBreak and FreeTimeBreak.
edas#MealBreak: BreakEvent is the parent of MealBreak which is the equivalent of CoffeeBreak.
edas#Reviewer: The ConferenceChair and the SessionChair are both children of AcceptedPaper. The paper is being reviewed by the TPCMember who is the parent of the Paper. The CallForReviews is initiated by the SessionChair and is related to the AcademicEvent.
edas#ClosingTalk: ClosingTalk is the parent of TalkEvent and WelcomeTalk.
edas#WelcomeTalk: TalkEvent and ConferenceEvent are parented by TalkEvent and ConferenceEvent. Both ConferenceEvent and ConferenceEvent are children of AcademicEvent. PaperPresentation and AcceptedPaper are related to PaperPresentation.
edas#TalkEvent: TalkEvent is the parent of ClosingTalk and WelcomeTalk.
edas#SessionChair: TPCMember is the parent of the SessionChair who initiates the call isInitiatedBy. The call is also initiated by the ConferenceChair who is the parent of the TPCMember. The Reviewer is the equivalent of the Author and the SessionChair is the parent of the SessionChair.
edas#TPCMember: The TPCMember is the parent of the document which is a child of the document. Paper is the parent of the document which is a child of the document. The person is the equivalent of the reviewer and the author.
edas#CallForPapers: CallForPapers is initiated by the ConferenceChair and TPCMember. TPCMember is the parent of the ConferenceChair and attendeeAt a ConferenceEvent.
edas#TextualReviewQuestion: ReviewQuestion is a child of TextualReviewQuestion and NumericalReviewQuestion.
edas#NumericalReviewQuestion: ReviewQuestion is the parent of NumericalReviewQuestion and TextualReviewQuestion.
edas#OrganizationalMeeting: AcademicEvent is the parent of OrganizationalMeeting and PaperPresentation.
edas#PaperPresentation: PaperPresentation is the parent of AcademicEvent and ConferenceEvent. It is also the parent of RejectedPaper and ConferenceEvent. RejectedPaper is also the parent of SocialEvent and ConferenceEvent.
edas#Workshop: The ConferenceEvent is the parent of the AcademicEvent and the ConferenceChair. The ConferenceEvent has an attendee who is a child of the Conference Chair. The ConferenceEvent has a programme which is the parent of the document.
edas#AcademicEvent: ConferenceEvent is the parent of both AcademicEvent and MealEvent. BreakEvent is the equivalent of CoffeeBreak and is also the parent of FreeTimeBreak. WithdrawnPaper and PaperPresentation are both children of ConferenceEvent.
edas#PersonalPublicationHistory: PersonalHistory is the parent of PersonalPublicationHistory. It is the child of PersonalReviewHistory which is the equivalent of a Reviewer who is reviewing a paper.
edas#Excursion: SocialEvent is the parent of Excursion and Reception.
edas#SocialEvent: SocialEvent is a child of Excursion and Reception.
edas#CallForReviews: CallForReviews is parented to ConferenceChair and ConferenceEvent Attendee. The ConferenceChair is the parent of CallForManuscripts which was initiated by CallForReviews.
edas#PersonalReviewHistory: PersonalReviewHistory is the parent of PersonalReviewHistory which is the child of PersonalPublicationHistory which is the parent of PersonalReviewHistory. The Reviewer is the equivalent of Person.
edas#ConferenceVenuePlace: ConferenceEvent is a non-academic event. It is also the parent of TalkEvent and ConferenceVenuePlace. It is also the parent of AccommodationPlace which is the parent of ConferenceEvent. PaperPresentation and ConferenceEvent are both children of ConferenceEvent.
edas#CallForManuscripts: CallForManuscripts is the parent of CallForReviews which is initiated by TPCMember. Paper is a child of ActivePaper and PublishedPaper.
edas#Reception: SocialEvent is the parent of ConferenceEvent and Excursion. SocialEvent is also the parent of ConferenceEvent and Excursion.
edas#MeetingRoomPlace: ConferenceEvent is the parent of ConferenceVenuePlace which is located at isLocationOf. ConferenceEvent is also the parent of SocialEvent and AcademicEvent. PaperPresentation and TalkEvent are both children of AcademicEvent.
edas#AccommodationPlace: AccommodationPlace is the parent of ConferenceVenuePlace and is the child of ConferenceVenuePlace.
edas#RatedPapers: WithdrawnPaper is a document that is relating to a person. It is parented to both WithdrawnPaper and AccpetIfRoomRating which is the equivalent of ReviewRating. RejectRating is the parent of AccpetIfRoomRating which is the equivalent of ReviewRating.
edas#TravelGrant: TravelGrant is the parent of Sponsorship which is a child of TravelGrant.
edas#ConferenceDinner: ConferenceDinner is parented by MealEvent and SocialEvent. Excursion and ConferenceEvent are both children of SocialEvent.
